 :tx/rationale "CCE LIFECYCLE WIRING PROPOSAL: Wire the 8 dead kernel functions into the CLI at two integration points. INTEGRATION POINT 1 — OBSERVE (on concept join): When assign_to_concept returns Joined, the CLI must: (a) Compute surprise_weight(surprise, alpha) from the assignment. (b) Call update_centroid_weighted(old_centroid, old_total_weight, obs_embedding, weight) to get new centroid. (c) Write updated :concept/embedding (new centroid), :concept/member-count (increment), :concept/total-weight (accumulate), :concept/variance (recompute from centroid distance). These datoms go in the SAME CCE follow-up transaction. The concept is now a LIVING entity that evolves with each observation. INTEGRATION POINT 2 — HARVEST (crystallize uncategorized): At harvest time, after collecting harvest candidates: (a) Find all observations with :exploration/embedding but WITHOUT :exploration/concept (uncategorized). (b) Collect their embeddings and body texts. (c) Call crystallize_concepts(observations, JOIN_THRESHOLD, MIN_CLUSTER_SIZE). (d) For each NewConcept: call concept_to_datoms + membership_datoms, write to store. (e) Report: '3 new concepts crystallized: event-processing, error-handling, deployment'. New emergent concepts then participate in future assign_to_concept calls. This IS the ontology discovery loop. INTEGRATION POINT 3 — STATUS (lifecycle checks): After concept_inventory: (a) For each concept with variance > SPLIT_THRESHOLD, recommend split: 'concept:X may need splitting (variance=0.63)'. (b) For each pair with should_merge, recommend merge: 'concepts X and Y are highly similar (cosine=0.91)'. These are RECOMMENDATIONS, not automatic actions — the agent decides. VERIFICATION: (A) After 5 observations about 'event sourcing', the event-related innate concept shows member_count=5 (not 0). (B) After 10 diverse observations, harvest crystallizes at least 1 new concept. (C) braid status shows accurate member counts, not static zeros. (D) Surprise-weighted centroids shift toward surprising members."
